HEADWORD: Untune
<hw>Un*tune"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>tune</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make incapable of
harmony, or of harmonious action; to put out of tune.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

